BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:openai-economic-research-exchange-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T105922Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: OpenAI Economic Research Exchange 2026
DESCRIPTION:The OpenAI Economic Research Exchange is a new program supporti
 ng high-impact external research on the economic effects of AI. Through th
 e Exchange\, selected researchers conduct work via structured\, project-ba
 sed collaborations with OpenAI Economic Research\, with the goal of produc
 ing credible\, independent evidence on how AI is affecting workers\, firms
 \, institutions\, and the broader economy. OpenAI is seeking projects that
  address important questions about the economic impacts of AI\; proposals 
 should explain how carefully governed\, privacy-protected use of OpenAI to
 ols and datasets can help answer these questions\, extending beyond what t
 raditional datasets alone allow\, while maintaining clear safeguards for u
 ser privacy and responsible data use. Core questions include labor market 
 effects (moving beyond AI exposure to measure which occupations are likely
  to see augmentation\, displacement\, new task creation\, or employment gr
 owth as model capabilities improve) and measuring economic value (willingn
 ess to pay\, revealed value\, task-level time savings\, avoided costs\, qu
 ality-adjusted output\, and durable productivity gains). Selected research
 ers undertake carefully scoped projects with defined milestones\, data gov
 ernance\, and review processes. WHO SHOULD APPLY: researchers with strong 
 empirical skills and relevant expertise in applied causal inference\, meas
 urement\, labor economics\, productivity\, firms\, education\, entrepreneu
 rship\, public finance\, regional economics\, development\, inequality\, o
 r related fields. EVALUATION: proposals are assessed on methodological rig
 or\, feasibility\, fit with Exchange priorities\, clear milestones\, and t
 he potential to contribute credible external evidence on AI's economic imp
 acts. The Exchange builds on OpenAI's broader measurement efforts\, includ
 ing OpenAI Signals. For more information see the Request for Proposals\, o
 r contact econresearch@openai.com. Applications close 5 July 2026\; select
 ed researchers will be notified by 31 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: OpenAI\n
 Location: Remote / global. Structured\, project-based research collaborati
 ons with OpenAI Economic Research. No location restriction stated.\nAward:
  USD 25\,000 project grant plus a USD 7\,500 monthly stipend per selected 
 researcher.\nDuration: Carefully scoped projects with defined milestones. 
 OpenAI supports a portfolio across time horizons: short-term projects (2-6
  months) using existing approved data\, and medium-term studies (6-12 mont
 hs) that track outcomes over time or test specific interventions.\n\nMore:
  https://openai.com/index/economic-research-exchange-request-for-proposals
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://openai.com/index/economic-research-exchange-request-for-proposa
 ls/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote / global. Structured\, project-based research collaboration
 s with OpenAI Economic Research. No location restriction stated.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tech-to-the-rescue-ai-impact-scaling-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T105922Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: AI Impact Scaling Program 2026 (Tech To The Rescue)
DESCRIPTION:The AI Impact Scaling Program from Tech To The Rescue helps non
 profits and social impact organizations use AI to expand the reach and eff
 ectiveness of interventions that already demonstrate measurable results. T
 he focus is scaling proven impact\, not proving it. Selected organizations
  get access to an ecosystem designed to turn proven programs into scalable
  AI-powered solutions\, including: a matched pro bono technology partner f
 rom a network of 2\,000+ software companies and AI experts\; scaling strat
 egy support and a tailored AI roadmap\; specialized guidance on responsibl
 e AI\, cybersecurity\, and data governance\; access to mentors\, infrastru
 cture credits\, and technical resources\; and visibility with funders and 
 investors through a global Demo Day. The program estimates participating o
 rganizations receive between USD 150\,000 and USD 330\,000 worth of servic
 es at no cost. WHO SHOULD APPLY: organizations with a proven intervention\
 , real users\, measurable outcomes\, and clear potential to scale\; NGOs a
 nd social impact organizations from around the world\; teams able to dedic
 ate a project lead for at least five hours per week over the 12-month prog
 ram. You do not need to have an AI solution already built\; the program he
 lps identify where AI can accelerate impact and then build the solution al
 ongside experienced technology partners. Application deadline 30 June 2026
 .\n\nOrganisation: Tech To The Rescue\nLocation: NGOs and social impact or
 ganizations from around the world. Requires a project lead able to commit 
 at least 5 hours per week over the 12-month program.\nAward: No-cost progr
 am. Participating organizations are estimated to receive between USD 150\,
 000 and USD 330\,000 worth of services at no cost\, including a matched pr
 o bono technology partner\, scaling strategy support\, a tailored AI roadm
 ap\, responsible-AI/cybersecurity/data-governance guidance\, mentors\, inf
 rastructure credits\, technical resources\, and visibility with funders an
 d investors via a global Demo Day.\nDuration: 12-month program.\n\nMore: h
 ttps://techtotherescue.org/ai-impact-scaling-program?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
