DTSTAMP:20260722T105922Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: Jamverse Jam (Protocolized worldbuilding contest)
DESCRIPTION:Protocolized's fourth contest invites artists and writers (stor
 ytellers\, poets\, comic artists) to build\, extend\, and connect the Jamv
 erse\, a shared near-future science fiction universe of four intersecting 
 story cycles (The Stockton Chronicles\, Legends and Ledgers\, UET-Trainver
 se\, and Zoothesia). ELIGIBILITY: open to anyone\; you may submit up to th
 ree in-universe worldbuilding artifacts\, and the same creator can win mul
 tiple prizes. REQUIREMENTS: each artifact must be under 1\,000 words (200-
 700 is the sweet spot) or a visual equivalent (comic panel\, poster\, adve
 rtisement\, etc.) and must include at least one element drawn from one of 
 the four sub-world 'toy boxes'\, a surprising 'traffic jam' (an emergent\,
  ah-ha consequence of a technology or protocol)\, and a relation to the th
 eme of Stigmergy (indirect coordination through modifying a shared environ
 ment). Artifact types can include comic panels\, job postings\, poems\, fo
 rum threads\, historic documents\, or encyclopedia entries. APPLY: submit 
 each artifact as a public Google Doc via the contest form\, including the 
 artifact\, a one-paragraph explanation of the worlds/toy-box components us
 ed and how the piece relates to stigmergy and explores a traffic jam\, and
 \, if AI was used\, documentation of your AI/LLM protocol. PRIZES: one USD
  1\,000 grand prize and at least 10 USD 200 prizes\, all published on the 
 Jamverse website. DEADLINE: 31 July 2026. Contest rules\, the current Jamv
 erse stories\, and starter materials are on the Jamverse website.\n\nOrgan
 isation: Protocolized (Summer of Protocols)\nLocation: Online / Worldwide\
 nAward: One USD 1\,000 grand prize plus at least 10 additional USD 200 pri
 zes\; winning artifacts are published on the Jamverse website. No entry fe
 e.\nDuration: One-off contest\; submit up to three artifacts by 31 July 20
 26\n\nMore: https://protocolized.summerofprotocols.com/p/jamverse-jam?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://protocolized.summerofprotocols.com/p/jamverse-jam?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online / Worldwide
END:VEVENT
