DTSTAMP:20260722T105922Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260925
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260926
SUMMARY:Deadline: Future Vision XPRIZE (sci-fi film competition)
DESCRIPTION:Future Vision XPRIZE is a sci-fi film competition challenging f
 ilmmakers to portray an optimistic\, abundant future for humanity rather t
 han a dystopian one. CHALLENGE: create a 3-minute sci-fi trailer that depi
 cts a bold\, original\, hopeful vision of progress. PRIZES: USD 3.5 millio
 n-plus total\; the grand prize winner gets USD 2.6 million-plus to turn th
 eir trailer into a feature film\, plus over USD 1 million in prizes for ru
 nners-up. BACKGROUND: launched by the nonprofit XPRIZE and funded by Peter
  Diamandis\, with Google and Range as partners\; inspired by the optimism 
 of Star Trek and intended to give storytellers a hopeful 'north star' for 
 builders. TIMELINE: competition launched 9 March 2026\; finals on 25 Septe
 mber 2026 in Los Angeles (finalists attend in person). APPLY: register and
  read the rules on the contest website. NOTE: confirm the exact submission
  deadline\, eligibility\, and team rules on futurevisionxprize.com\; the 2
 5 September 2026 date listed here is the finals event date.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: XPRIZE (Future Vision XPRIZE\, funded by Peter Diamandis\; partners Goo
 gle and Range)\nLocation: Online / Worldwide (finals held in Los Angeles)\
 nAward: USD 3.5 million-plus prize pool. Grand prize winner receives USD 2
 .6 million-plus to develop their vision into a feature film\, with over US
 D 1 million in additional prizes for runners-up.\nDuration: One-off compet
 ition\; create a 3-minute sci-fi trailer\n\nMore: https://futurevisionxpri
 ze.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://futurevisionxprize.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online / Worldwide (finals held in Los Angeles)
